PIENAAR –   According to police flying squad unit leader Capt Pieter Smit, the vehicle was on its way to do its last pick up for the day. The vehicle was ambushed on the road by about 12 to 15 suspects who opened fire on the driver and the crew of the security vehicle bringing it to a halt.  The driver and the crew were injured during the shootout. The suspects then bombed the back of the vehicle and fled the scene with an undisclosed amount of money.  